<FAQ title="Frequently Asked Questions" items={[
  { question: "How long does a complete bathroom renovation take?", answer: "A full bathroom renovation takes between 2 and 4 weeks. This includes demolition, waterproofing, plumbing, electrical work, tiling, and fixture installation." },
  { question: "What type of waterproofing do you use?", answer: "We apply continuous-layer waterproofing systems with a 10-year warranty, covering shower areas, wet walls, and floors using certified materials." },
  { question: "Can I keep the current bathroom layout?", answer: "Yes, we can renovate while maintaining the existing layout or propose a new one. Moving fixtures requires plumbing changes and may affect the budget." },
  { question: "Do you include debris removal?", answer: "Yes, our service includes demolition, debris removal, and final cleaning. We leave your bathroom ready to use without any hassle on your end." }
]} />

